Package graphql.cachecontrol

Class CacheControl

  • java.lang.Object
    • graphql.cachecontrol.CacheControl
  • @PublicApi
public class CacheControl
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements the graphql Cache Control specification as outlined in https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-cache-control

    To best use this class you need to pass a CacheControl object to each DataFetcher and have them decide on the caching hint values.

    The easiest why to do this is create a CacheControl object at query start and pass it in as a "context" object via ExecutionInput.getContext() and then have each DataFetcher thats wants to make cache control hints use that.

    Then at the end of the query you would call addTo(graphql.ExecutionResult) to record the cache control hints into the ExecutionResult extensions map as per the specification.

      static class  CacheControl.Scope
      If the scope is set to PRIVATE, this indicates anything under this path should only be cached per-user, unless the value is overridden on a sub path.
